results.name: Exponent of highest power of 5 dividing n. Or, 5-adic valuation of n.
comment: This is also the 5-adic valuation of Fibonacci(n). See Lengyel link. - _Michel Marcus_, May 06 2017
link: Reinhard Zumkeller, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
T. Lengyel, The order of the Fibonacci and Lucas numbers, Fibonacci Quart. 33 (1995), no. 3, 234-239. See Lemma 1 p. 235.
formula: Totally additive with a(p) = 1 if p = 5, 0 otherwise.
Asymptotic mean: lim_{m->oo} (1/m) * Sum_{k=1..m} a(k) = 1/4. - _Amiram Eldar_, Feb 14 2021
program: | otherwise = fives n' (e + 1) where (n',r) = divMod n 5
results.author: _Reinhard Zumkeller_, Sep 18 2005
